
% Builtin lemma for un-mangling of functional relations

% functional relations

functional1(p) is axiom ~p(X,Y) | ~p(X,Y2) | Y=Y2.
total1(p, f) is axiom p(X,f(X)).
functional2(p) is axiom ~p(X,Y,Z) | ~p(X,Y,Z2) | Z=Z2.
total2(p, f) is axiom p(X,Y,f(X,Y)).

lemma p(X,Y) <=> Y=f(X) if functional1(p) and total1(p, f).
lemma p(X,Y,Z) <=> Z = f(X,Y) if functional2(p) and total2(p, f).

